[It has been suggested to me that an African would have most credibility in West Africa as global coordinator of the anti-EVD struggle, being more likely to understand the political and cultural constraints on the ground. Kofi Annan of Ghana, former Secretary-General of the United Nations and a skilled negotiator, was still active as the UN-Arab League Joint Special Representative for Syria until August 2012. He may already have been approached.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map with the latest case locations and counts is available at http://healthmap.org/ebola. - Mod.JW]
